crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This is a MIPS variant of the Mozi botnet, a P2P IoT malware. It propagates by scanning for and exploiting numerous vulnerabilities in routers and other IoT devices. Upon successful exploitation, it downloads and executes further payloads. The sample contains many hardcoded exploit strings and payload download commands. Key indicators include the presence of strings like `/Mozi.m`, `/Mozi.a`, and attempts to exploit protocols like HNAP (`purenetworks.com/HNAP1/`) and GPON (`/GponForm/diag_Form`). It also establishes persistence by modifying startup scripts (e.g., `/etc/rc.local`) and manipulates `iptables` to allow its C2 traffic.
